cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.NA, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on developing an efficient deterministic parallel algorithm, which is suitable for distributed implementation. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an algorithm for solving the minimum-weight vertex- and set-cover problems and their duals, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.Distributed - The paper's focus on distributed implementation and parallel algorithms makes it relevant to the Distributed sub-category. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper mentions the use of linear-programming primal-dual approximation techniques, which are commonly used in numerical analysis. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper's focus on the duals of vertex- and set-cover problems (edge/element packing) makes it relevant to the Game Theory sub-category.
